[
  {
    "id": "PRO.3.1",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "My son, forget not my law; but let thine heart keep my commandments:",
    "hash": "2b9c85071c631572bb3a17b5519c4f1910d07ecbc06a19f5b7dd326ea2b03242"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.3.2",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "For length of days, and long life, and peace, shall they add to thee. {long...: Heb. years of life}",
    "hash": "a3e6e87a714381564af32614e6eab4d01dcf2e1d2eac8a5e1ad218a57407929c"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.3.3",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "Let not mercy and truth forsake thee: bind them about thy neck; write them upon the table of thine heart:",
    "hash": "382387be303f53b951354a4439f4059ed1e43994aaf95bb1ff20b431c127836a"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.3.4",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "So shalt thou find favour and good understanding in the sight of God and man. {good...: or, good success}",
    "hash": "464ffd7827b5917a0058e4d6bffa4933ac7cc7c8145fce3a48c31d498d3de64f"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.3.5",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "Trust in the LORD with all thine heart; and lean not unto thine own understanding.",
    "hash": "848c7aaeb9ee74bafece4baae92593a800f7ad683d8daaae9dc3cd1ded0dfdbd"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.3.6",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "In all thy ways acknowledge him, and he shall direct thy paths.",
    "hash": "ddeb25ba4651a996c0c6cdce40cd7abf157da225173a7a5a270a82b832aaa37f"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.3.7",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "Be not wise in thine own eyes: fear the LORD, and depart from evil.",
    "hash": "b05cf5211229b46c91e9386bde3a96438f2570c4d3afd2d7c6b98a12ee6367fa"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.3.8",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "It shall be health to thy navel, and marrow to thy bones. {health: Heb. medicine} {marrow: Heb. watering, or, moistening}",
    "hash": "558b4484fe1d03f820c4eac053d06b803b8342b305b472e6c147cf25e5471d0e"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.3.9",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "Honour the LORD with thy substance, and with the firstfruits of all thine increase:",
    "hash": "927b685cdade956e8e59d3e469fe19ee72aae76bd75ba000d9d785583cf27f21"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.3.10",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "So shall thy barns be filled with plenty, and thy presses shall burst out with new wine.",
    "hash": "3fdd36685948962e382c9884f0bb238ca5deec6d05028e8649f2729610b083e6"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.3.11",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "My son, despise not the chastening of the LORD; neither be weary of his correction:",
    "hash": "3c365bc8bc8dea27b727df83ad9b4215e632f1fdf339ac1f13ba5c266ddb9dfe"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.3.12",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "For whom the LORD loveth he correcteth; even as a father the son {in whom} he delighteth.",
    "hash": "2ff7850db82e4bd52e55708d01c9f5cba95b6298398f3166d8a2548e7742550b"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.3.13",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "Happy {is} the man {that} findeth wisdom, and the man {that} getteth understanding. {that getteth...: Heb. that draweth out understanding}",
    "hash": "8bb5af54aa68627907c35ff2f1e6035ecfd7a913f465f22cc0668adcb7caa617"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.3.14",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "For the merchandise of it {is} better than the merchandise of silver, and the gain thereof than fine gold.",
    "hash": "77562efc46d2265b8a895ff7b56a261a70f4ef77226cb66901a33ffbe4c2342b"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.3.15",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "She {is} more precious than rubies: and all the things thou canst desire are not to be compared unto her.",
    "hash": "1258edbbb60c5c88e8c0c4fad0ec62757fb64d72afd3a35cae2ee869564733dc"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.3.16",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "Length of days {is} in her right hand; {and} in her left hand riches and honour.",
    "hash": "2cfde7d2ba9c8d7fe1045b4ae8d056408fd0c5b6104997ecf5e6d53d020f91cb"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.3.17",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "Her ways {are} ways of pleasantness, and all her paths {are} peace.",
    "hash": "9c5d4e68726a735a3c8b79671ad0ed61f27dd8f2be11be016d31b0355c2b6081"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.3.18",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "She {is} a tree of life to them that lay hold upon her: and happy {is every one} that retaineth her.",
    "hash": "2647a810c61f2d2c6e85e0880bdd3f9e4dd2b5dcf68033da2ff79a442e57eef2"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.3.19",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "The LORD by wisdom hath founded the earth; by understanding hath he established the heavens. {established: or, prepared}",
    "hash": "18ccba7b80c665bc604b921f683d2ca23a1ce4e7ae2b3bb5aa06bfd0eab48444"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.3.20",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "By his knowledge the depths are broken up, and the clouds drop down the dew.",
    "hash": "8c75741cc3d03b624f78abf6197e4023696af1f5b37afdc1ef18acc91398c0c1"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.3.21",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "My son, let not them depart from thine eyes: keep sound wisdom and discretion:",
    "hash": "c4fd91882103a2daf2cdd41e034d608bc015e92461d532835c86711978e43edc"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.3.22",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "So shall they be life unto thy soul, and grace to thy neck.",
    "hash": "4189ad216ec3b7d6c6cb449370eed61b84e1b94b852ed99f02cd6c53f859a27e"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.3.23",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "Then shalt thou walk in thy way safely, and thy foot shall not stumble.",
    "hash": "0394d92eaa1776fdc8727b71533b8c3a94b0d86f690f4559e50c0707d76d8589"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.3.24",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "When thou liest down, thou shalt not be afraid: yea, thou shalt lie down, and thy sleep shall be sweet.",
    "hash": "6772b33b96a5caab8db7a1edba1a6fc31b8ff3f82b86021089c8ff79c7d4af56"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.3.25",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "Be not afraid of sudden fear, neither of the desolation of the wicked, when it cometh.",
    "hash": "17f6f1014a33377468c3b22fcba579a1c9ca166176b286f2a1e2d1a7737ed9d9"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.3.26",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "For the LORD shall be thy confidence, and shall keep thy foot from being taken.",
    "hash": "31e4fd17a5e146c815312b8c50d79c44baa3f696f8cf5da2a029f089377265af"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.3.27",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "Withhold not good from them to whom it is due, when it is in the power of thine hand to do {it}. {them...: Heb. the owners thereof}",
    "hash": "7234925f65ed73b9ab1c285539dde12a8a984d8fd237c5f7814a8f3ca83f1504"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.3.28",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "Say not unto thy neighbour, Go, and come again, and to morrow I will give; when thou hast it by thee.",
    "hash": "6414c04178e5b26c43984eb3eb6db2342783d883709e0aaaaa2af84596103f03"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.3.29",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "Devise not evil against thy neighbour, seeing he dwelleth securely by thee. {Devise...: or, Practise no evil}",
    "hash": "bdb9e6cddc922eb9dcde2884153f878576dfee22c23979dce47074fb1f79428b"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.3.30",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "Strive not with a man without cause, if he have done thee no harm.",
    "hash": "606e845cd99a8a6c43a9e7bb34b1b231d21f4270fd3d47ffb5c899d85ca22b52"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.3.31",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "Envy thou not the oppressor, and choose none of his ways. {the oppressor: Heb. a man of violence}",
    "hash": "cece8702175371488042773d3eb6c352100c03abb911647af4b1f2ae2a1d7e94"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.3.32",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 32,
    "text": "For the froward {is} abomination to the LORD: but his secret {is} with the righteous.",
    "hash": "9b27ac888ee222b9e72b5dcc28522962848f3a3792ff02cb745818da88f86d37"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.3.33",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 33,
    "text": "The curse of the LORD {is} in the house of the wicked: but he blesseth the habitation of the just.",
    "hash": "a94817af11fd34b94f373b8e30266fdf21a3a17b55b69d08e79dbfe4b35d582b"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.3.34",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 34,
    "text": "Surely he scorneth the scorners: but he giveth grace unto the lowly.",
    "hash": "3658356672313a0b5f052bb49cb52b33b2e473e3faf113872d00f2bc0c7e091f"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.3.35",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 35,
    "text": "The wise shall inherit glory: but shame shall be the promotion of fools. {shall be...: Heb. exalteth the fools}",
    "hash": "04113dc5dcb4e953965130ab600f40b0d4b5fa2e737e8884a41ded108a4e8790"
  }
]